 mistaken for other behaviors.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051904,0.085034,0.092972,0.10227,0.093985,0.091403,0.091825,0.089805,0.086366,0.080479,0.072362,0.061595],"unified_progress":[0.048419,0.077265,0.091777,0.099299,0.099597,0.098693,0.097285,0.094936,0.089715,0.084143,0.069467,0.049402]},{"section":6,"text":"Next, the child has early onset of puberty.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044281,0.075314,0.081897,0.083217,0.091801,0.093773,0.093475,0.09409,0.091527,0.092979,0.083224,0.074422],"unified_progress":[0.044165,0.073876,0.085562,0.095029,0.09629,0.099459,0.0992,0.095441,0.090094,0.087961,0.074029,0.058893]},{"section":7,"text":"Precocious puberty in a child can be due to various factors, including central causes where the brain starts producing hormones too early.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032108,0.055011,0.072777,0.082403,0.094861,0.10117,0.10692,0.10852,0.10648,0.097374,0.081166,0.061211],"unified_progress":[0.03198,0.058948,0.083224,0.093192,0.1011,0.11271,0.1069,0.1039,0.097099,0.090543,0.069854,0.050549]},{"section":8,"text":"The hypothalamus plays a key role in triggering puberty by releasing gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH), which then stimulates the pituitary gland to release gonadotropins, leading to the development of secondary sexual characteristics.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041348,0.056709,0.072127,0.08315,0.094295,0.099986,0.10555,0.10582,0.10263,0.092923,0.080167,0.065295],"unified_progress":[0.039283,0.064277,0.081768,0.092459,0.099741,0.10489,0.10262,0.10031,0.096825,0.088997,0.073777,0.055055]},{"section":9,"text":"The physical examination didn't show any focal neurological deficits, which suggests that the issue isn't localized to a specific area of the brain but might be more central.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042191,0.067053,0.080632,0.